&gt; Cannot assign to &#39;Btn&#39; because it is a &#39;foreach iteration variable&#39;

Mistakes
1. The error happened because you assign a defined iteration variable to a new variable in C#, it&#39;s not allowed
2. You can&#39;t assign a string value, &quot;Btn&quot; is a string type, so if you do like that, the expression will be
 &quot;Q1_Button_1&quot; = true;
   Which is illegal and in Python, it&#39;s get exception

Instead of four different variables, you should use an array:

    bool[] QButton_True = new bool[4];
    for (int i = 0 ; i &lt; 4 ; i++) {
        QButton_True[i] = true;
    }

Instead of referring to them as `Q1Button_True`, `Q2Button_True`..., you refer to them as `QButton_True[0]`, `QButton_True[1]`...

